183class SetInitialFocus {
184public:
185 using Arguments = std::tuple<bool, bool, const WebKit::WebKeyboardEvent&>;
186
187 static IPC::MessageName name() { return IPC::MessageName::WebPage_SetInitialFocus; }
188 static constexpr bool isSync = false;
189
190 static void callReply(IPC::Decoder&, CompletionHandler<void()>&&);
191 static void cancelReply(CompletionHandler<void()>&&);
192 static IPC::MessageName asyncMessageReplyName() { return IPC::MessageName::WebPage_SetInitialFocusReply; }
193 using AsyncReply = SetInitialFocusAsyncReply;
194 static constexpr auto callbackThread = WTF::CompletionHandlerCallThread::ConstructionThread;
195 static void send(UniqueRef<IPC::Encoder>&&, IPC::Connection&);
196 using Reply = std::tuple<>;
197 using ReplyArguments = std::tuple<>;
198 SetInitialFocus(bool forward, bool isKeyboardEventValid, const WebKit::WebKeyboardEvent& event)
199 : m_arguments(forward, isKeyboardEventValid, event)
200 {
201 }
202
203 const Arguments& arguments() const
204 {
205 return m_arguments;
206 }
207
208private:
209 Arguments m_arguments;
210};
